'''Darius Aaron Morris''' (born January 3, 1991) is an [[United States|American]] professional basketball [[point guard]] for the [[Los Angeles Lakers]] of the [[National Basketball Association]]. Morris was selected as the 41st pick to the Los Angeles Lakers in the [[2011 NBA Draft]].

Morris had completed his sophomore season with the [[Michigan Wolverines men's basketball|Michigan Wolverines basketball team]] for the [[2010<U+2013>11 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2010<U+2013>11 team]]. He was the [[2010<U+2013>11 Big Ten Conference men's basketball season|2010<U+2013>11 Big Ten]] [[assist (basketball)|assists]] leader and is Michigan Wolverines all-time single-season assist record-holder. He earned third team All-Big Ten honors as a sophomore.

Morris led [[Windward School]] to the 2009 state championship while earning the [[California Interscholastic Federation]] (CIF) Southern Section [[John R. Wooden Award#High School Player of the Year Award|John Wooden High School Player of the Year Award]]. He was a 2010<U+2013>11 All-Big Ten 3rd team selection by the coaches and the media. The [[National Association of Basketball Coaches]] named him as a 2nd team  All-District selection for the district composed of Big Ten schools.

==High School==
In high school, Morris, the son of Dewayne Sr. and Robin Morris, attended [[Windward School]].  Morris was invited to numerous All-star basketball camps hosted by [[LeBron James]], [[Steve Nash]], the [[National Basketball Players Association]] and [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]. He was twice selected as a first-team All-State player in California.  He was also named the MVP of numerous tournaments and invited to participate in numerous All-star games, including the Academic All-American Classic.<ref NAME=4DM>{{cite web|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5ztW9aMHx|archivedate=2011-07-03|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/morris_darius00.html|title=4 Darius Morris|accessdate=2011-03-07|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref> Morris led Windward High School to the California Division V state title, posting a game-high 25 points, eight rebounds and four assists in the championship game.<ref NAME=4DM/> Darius Morris was named the MVP of Olympic League, CIF Division 5A Southern Section Player of Year,<ref>{{vcite web|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:ENTB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=1275071F76126840&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Snaer, Leonard share top D1AA honors|accessdate=April 12, 2009|date=March 31, 2009|work=[[The Press-Enterprise]]}}</ref> and CIF Division 5A State Player of Year. Also Darius was awarded a John Wooden High School Player of the Year Award,<ref>{{vcite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/varsitytimesinsider/2009/04/boys-basketball-leonard-among-wooden-award-winners.html|title=Boys' basketball: Leonard among Wooden Award winners|accessdate=April 12, 2009|date=April 07, 2009|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Bolch, Ben}}</ref> received by [[Jrue Holiday]] the year before.<ref>{{vcite web|url=http://woodenaward.cstv.com/ot/award-high-school.html|title=High School Winners|accessdate=April 12, 2009|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref> He was ranked as the 11th, 15th and 20th best [[high school basketball]] point guard in the nation by [[ESPN]], [[Rivals.com]] and [[Scout.com]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/recruiting/player/_/id/42995|title=Darius Morris|accessdate=2011-03-07|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref name=DMRdc>{{cite web|url=http://rivals.yahoo.com/basketballrecruiting/basketball/recruiting/player-Darius-Morris-67844;_ylt=AgYjdC0.PSNI.N3bG8qkZE7SO5B4|title=Darius Morris|accessdate=2011-03-07|publisher=[[Rivals.com]]}}</ref><ref name=DMESPN>{{cite web|url=http://michigan.scout.com/a.z?s=162&p=8&c=1&nid=3222058|title=Darius Morris|accessdate=2011-03-07|publisher=[[Scout.com]]}}</ref> Rivals and ESPN included him on their lists of best overall basketball players at 77th and 100th, respectively.<ref name=DMRdc/><ref name=DMESPN/>
