As a freshman with the [[2009<U+2013>10 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2009<U+2013>10 team]], Morris averaged 4.4 [[point (basketball)|points]] and 2.6 assist per game on 24.3 minutes of playing time per game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/player/profile?playerId=45979|title=Darius Morris  #4  G|accessdate=2011-03-04|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Three times he scored in double digits, including his first career game.  He had a season-high 7 assists against [[2009<U+2013>10 Northwestern Wildcats men's basketball team|Northwestern]] on January 10, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/player/gamelog?playerId=45979&year=2010|title=Darius Morris  #4  G (2009-10 game log)|accessdate=2011-03-04|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>

On December 23, 2010, Morris was one of three Wolverines to make 4 [[three point shot]]s as the team set a school single-game record by making 16 against {{cbb link|2010|sex=men|team=Bryant Bulldogs|school=Bryant University|title=Bryant University}}.<ref name=BU7M8/><ref name=>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/mich/sports/m-baskbl/auto_pdf/bkm-all-time-records|title=All-Time Records|accessdate=2011-01-16|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com|page=8}}</ref> He also had 12 assists on his way to a [[double-double]].<ref name=BU7M8>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=303570130|title=Bryant U 71 (1-10, 0-1 NEC): Michigan 87 (10-2, 9-0 home)|accessdate=2011-02-03|date=2010-12-23|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> On December 27, 2010, the Big Ten Conference named Morris player of the week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/122710aac.html|title=Michigan and Ohio State Claim Weekly Conference Honors: Michigan and Ohio State earn conference recognition|accessdate=2010-12-28|date=2010-12-27|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref> [[Ann Arbor, Michigan|Ann Arbor]] media felt his omission from the 67-man 2011 [[Bob Cousy Award]] watchlist was a surpise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.annarbor.com/sports/um-basketball/the-list-of-cousy-award-candidates-omits-michigan-guard-darius-morris-and-has-other-questionable-cal/|title=Cousy Award watch list omits Michigan guard Darius Morris and has other questionable calls|accessdate=2011-02-03|date=2010-12-20|work=[[AnnArbor.com]]|author=Rothstein, Michael}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michigandaily.com/content/morris-left-cousy-award-watchlist|title=Morris left off Cousy Award watchlist|accessdate=2011-02-03|date=2010-12-20|work=[[Michigan Daily]]|author=Estes, Ben}}</ref>  Morris repeated as (co-)player of the week on January 31, 2011 sharing the award with [[Talor Battle]], after becoming the third [[Michigan Wolverines men's basketball]] player (following [[Gary Grant]] and [[Manny Harris]]) to record a [[triple double]].<ref name=MOSaPSECR>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/013111aaa.html|title=Michigan, Ohio State and Penn State Earn Conference Recognition: Michigan's Darius Morris and Penn State's Talor Battle share Player of the Week while Ohio State's Jared Sullinger earns Freshman of the Week honors.|accessdate=2011-02-01|date=2011-01-31|publisher=[[Big Ten Conference]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=310300130|title=Michigan 87, Iowa 73|accessdate=2011-02-01|date=2011-01-30|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> On February 1, 2011, ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' calculated that Morris was by far the most valuable player to his team among major conference players because his combined assists and [[field goal (basketball)|field goals]] account for over 53% of his team's points.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748703439504576116132745965592.html?mod=googlenews_wsj|title=College Basketball's One-Man Gangs |accessdate=2011-02-03|date=2011-02-01|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref>

